The paper discusses the importance of making software analytics models explainable to software practitioners, which is a key concern in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of explainable artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the limitations of complex models such as deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of understanding the rationale behind predictions, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social science (cs.SI).
